pillow (11.3.0-0ubuntu1~ppa1~noble1) noble; urgency=medium

  * Initial packaging of Pillow 11.3.0 for the Avalan PPA.
  * Noble ships python3-pil 10.2.0 (below Avalan's floor of 11.3.0)
    and Debian sid ships 12.2.0 (above Avalan's ceiling of < 12), so
    the rebuild pins the upstream 11.3.0 sdist.
  * Ship a quilt patch (pyproject-for-noble) that relaxes the
    upstream `setuptools>=77` build-system requirement to `>= 62`
    (Noble ships 68.x, which is enough for Pillow's _custom_build
    backend) and rewrites the PEP 639 `license = "MIT-CMU"` +
    `license-files = [...]` pair back to the legacy
    `license = { text = "MIT-CMU" }` table form. Wheel metadata is
    equivalent; no runtime impact.
  * First binary (arch-dependent) source package in the per-dep tree.
    Build-Depends carries the standard codec/library development
    headers Pillow's setup.py looks for at compile time
    (zlib1g-dev, libjpeg-dev, libtiff-dev, libwebp-dev,
    libfreetype-dev, liblcms2-dev, libopenjp2-7-dev). Optional
    headers (libimagequant-dev, libraqm-dev, libavif-dev,
    libxcb1-dev for screen capture, tk-dev for ImageTk) are not
    included in this rebuild; add them on demand if a downstream
    feature needs them.

 -- Avalan Packaging Team <avalan@avalan.ai>  Mon, 18 May 2026 20:00:00 -0300
